[{"text": "So I was privileged to train in transplantation", "start": 16.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "under two great surgical pioneers:", "start": 20.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thomas Starzl,", "start": 22.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who performed the world's first successful liver transplant", "start": 24.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in 1967,", "start": 27.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Sir Roy Calne,", "start": 29.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who performed the first liver transplant in the U.K.", "start": 31.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the following year.", "start": 34.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I returned to Singapore", "start": 37.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and, in 1990,", "start": 39.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "performed Asia's first successful", "start": 41.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "cadaveric liver transplant procedure,", "start": 43.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but against all odds.", "start": 46.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now when I look back,", "start": 49.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the transplant was actually the easiest part.", "start": 51.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Next, raising the money to fund the procedure.", "start": 55.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "But perhaps the most challenging part", "start": 59.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "was to convince the regulators --", "start": 63.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a matter which was debated in the parliament --", "start": 65.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "that a young female surgeon", "start": 69.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "be allowed the opportunity", "start": 71.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to pioneer for her country.", "start": 73.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But 20 years on,", "start": 76.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "my patient, Surinder,", "start": 78.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is Asia's longest surviving", "start": 80.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "cadaveric liver transplant to date.", "start": 82.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 85.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And perhaps more important,", "start": 89.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I am the proud godmother", "start": 92.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to her 14 year-old son.", "start": 94.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 96.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But not all patients on the transplant wait list", "start": 100.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are so fortunate.", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The truth is,", "start": 104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there are just simply not enough donor organs", "start": 106.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to go around.", "start": 108.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "As the demand for donor organs", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "continues to rise,", "start": 112.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in large part due to the aging population,", "start": 114.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the supply has remained relatively constant.", "start": 117.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In the United States alone,", "start": 121.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "100,000 men, women and children", "start": 123.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "are on the waiting list for donor organs,", "start": 127.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and more than a dozen die each day", "start": 130.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because of a lack of donor organs.", "start": 133.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The transplant community", "start": 136.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has actively campaigned in organ donation.", "start": 138.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the gift of life", "start": 141.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has been extended", "start": 143.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from brain-dead donors", "start": 145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to living, related donors --", "start": 147.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "relatives who might donate an organ", "start": 149.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or a part of an organ,", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like a split liver graft,", "start": 154.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to a relative or loved one.", "start": 156.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But as there was still a dire shortage of donor organs,", "start": 159.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the gift of life was then extended", "start": 162.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from living, related donors", "start": 164.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to now living, unrelated donors.", "start": 166.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And this then has given rise", "start": 169.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to unprecedented and unexpected", "start": 172.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "moral controversy.", "start": 175.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How can one distinguish", "start": 178.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a donation that is voluntary and altruistic", "start": 181.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from one that is forced or coerced", "start": 184.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from, for example,", "start": 187.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a submissive spouse, an in-law,", "start": 189.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a servant, a slave,", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "an employee?", "start": 194.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Where and how can we draw the line?", "start": 196.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In my part of the world,", "start": 200.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "too many people live below the poverty line.", "start": 203.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And in some areas,", "start": 206.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the commercial gifting of an organ", "start": 208.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in exchange for monetary reward", "start": 210.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has led to a flourishing trade", "start": 213.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in living, unrelated donors.", "start": 215.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Shortly after I performed the first liver transplant,", "start": 219.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I received my next assignment,", "start": 222.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and that was to go to the prisons", "start": 224.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to harvest organs", "start": 227.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from executed prisoners.", "start": 229.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was also pregnant at the time.", "start": 232.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Pregnancies are meant", "start": 235.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to be happy and fulfilling moments", "start": 237.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in any woman's life.", "start": 240.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But my joyful period", "start": 242.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was marred by solemn and morbid thoughts --", "start": 244.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "thoughts of walking through", "start": 249.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the prison's high-security death row,", "start": 251.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as this was the only route", "start": 254.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to take me to the makeshift operating room.", "start": 256.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And at each time,", "start": 260.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I would feel the chilling stares", "start": 262.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of condemned prisoners' eyes follow me.", "start": 265.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And for two years,", "start": 269.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I struggled with the dilemma", "start": 271.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of waking up at 4:30 am", "start": 273.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on a Friday morning,", "start": 275.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "driving to the prison,", "start": 277.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "getting down, gloved and scrubbed,", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "ready to receive the body", "start": 281.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of an executed prisoner,", "start": 284.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "remove the organs", "start": 286.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then transport these organs", "start": 288.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the recipient hospital", "start": 290.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then graft the gift of life", "start": 292.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to a recipient the same afternoon.", "start": 295.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "No doubt, I was informed,", "start": 298.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the consent had been obtained.", "start": 300.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But, in my life,", "start": 306.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the one fulfilling skill that I had", "start": 308.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "was now invoking feelings of conflict --", "start": 313.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "conflict ranging", "start": 317.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from extreme sorrow and doubt at dawn", "start": 319.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to celebratory joy", "start": 323.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at engrafting the gift of life at dusk.", "start": 325.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "In my team,", "start": 329.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the lives of one or two of my colleagues", "start": 331.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "were tainted by this experience.", "start": 334.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Some of us may have been sublimated,", "start": 337.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but really none of us remained the same.", "start": 340.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I was troubled", "start": 344.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the retrieval of organs from executed prisoners", "start": 347.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "was at least as morally controversial", "start": 351.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as the harvesting of stem cells", "start": 354.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from human embryos.", "start": 356.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And in my mind,", "start": 359.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I realized as a surgical pioneer", "start": 361.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the purpose of my position of influence", "start": 364.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was surely to speak up", "start": 367.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for those who have no influence.", "start": 369.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It made me wonder", "start": 372.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if there could be a better way --", "start": 374.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a way to circumvent death", "start": 376.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and yet deliver the gift of life", "start": 379.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that might exponentially impact", "start": 381.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "millions of patients worldwide.", "start": 384.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now just about that time,", "start": 388.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the practice of surgery evolved", "start": 390.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from big to small,", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from wide open incisions", "start": 394.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to keyhole procedures,", "start": 396.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "tiny incisions.", "start": 398.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And in transplantation, concepts shifted", "start": 401.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from whole organs to cells.", "start": 404.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In 1988, at the University of Minnesota,", "start": 407.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I participated in a small series", "start": 410.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of whole organ pancreas transplants.", "start": 413.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I witnessed the technical difficulty.", "start": 416.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And this inspired in my mind", "start": 419.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a shift from transplanting whole organs", "start": 421.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to perhaps transplanting cells.", "start": 425.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I thought to myself,", "start": 427.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "why not take the individual cells", "start": 429.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "out of the pancreas --", "start": 432.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the cells that secrete insulin to cure diabetes --", "start": 434.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and transplant these cells? --", "start": 437.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "technically a much simpler procedure", "start": 440.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than having to grapple with the complexities", "start": 442.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of transplanting a whole organ.", "start": 445.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And at that time,", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "stem cell research", "start": 450.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "had gained momentum,", "start": 452.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "following the isolation of the world's first", "start": 454.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "human embryonic stem cells", "start": 457.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the 1990s.", "start": 459.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The observation that stem cells, as master cells,", "start": 462.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "could give rise", "start": 465.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to a whole variety of different cell types --", "start": 467.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "heart cells, liver cells,", "start": 469.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "pancreatic islet cells --", "start": 471.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "captured the attention of the media", "start": 473.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and the imagination of the public.", "start": 476.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I too was fascinated", "start": 479.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by this new and disruptive cell technology,", "start": 481.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and this inspired a shift in my mindset,", "start": 484.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from transplanting whole organs", "start": 487.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to transplanting cells.", "start": 489.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And I focused my research on stem cells", "start": 492.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as a possible source", "start": 495.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for cell transplants.", "start": 497.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Today we realize", "start": 500.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that there are many different types of stem cells.", "start": 502.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Embryonic stem cells", "start": 505.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have occupied center stage,", "start": 507.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "chiefly because of their pluripotency --", "start": 509.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "that is their ease in differentiating", "start": 513.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "into a variety of different cell types.", "start": 516.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But the moral controversy", "start": 520.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "surrounding embryonic stem cells --", "start": 523.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the fact that these cells are derived", "start": 526.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from five-day old human embryos --", "start": 528.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has encouraged research", "start": 531.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into other types of stem cells.", "start": 533.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now to the ridicule of my colleagues,", "start": 536.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I inspired my lab", "start": 540.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to focus on what I thought", "start": 542.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was the most non-controversial source of stem cells,", "start": 545.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "adipose tissue, or fat, yes fat --", "start": 549.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "nowadays available in abundant supply --", "start": 552.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you and I, I think, would be very happy to get rid of anyway.", "start": 556.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Fat-derived stem cells", "start": 561.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are adult stem cells.", "start": 563.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And adult stem cells", "start": 565.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are found in you and me --", "start": 567.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in our blood, in our bone marrow,", "start": 569.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in our fat, our skin and other organs.", "start": 571.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And as it turns out,", "start": 574.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "fat is one of the best sources", "start": 576.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of adult stem cells.", "start": 578.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But adult stem cells", "start": 580.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are not embryonic stem cells.", "start": 582.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And here is the limitation:", "start": 585.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "adult stem cells are mature cells,", "start": 587.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and, like mature human beings,", "start": 590.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "these cells are more restricted in their thought", "start": 593.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and more restricted in their behavior", "start": 596.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and are unable to give rise", "start": 599.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the wide variety of specialized cell types,", "start": 601.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "as embryonic stem cells [can].", "start": 604.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But in 2007,", "start": 606.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "two remarkable individuals,", "start": 609.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Shinya Yamanaka of Japan", "start": 612.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and Jamie Thomson of the United States,", "start": 614.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "made an astounding discovery.", "start": 617.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They discovered", "start": 620.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that adult cells, taken from you and me,", "start": 622.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "could be reprogrammed", "start": 625.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "back into embryonic-like cells,", "start": 628.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which they termed IPS cells,", "start": 630.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or induced pluripotent stem cells.", "start": 633.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "And so guess what,", "start": 638.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "scientists around the world and in the labs", "start": 640.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are racing", "start": 643.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to convert aging adult cells --", "start": 645.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "aging adult cells from you and me --", "start": 648.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they are racing to reprogram these cells", "start": 650.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "back into more useful IPS cells.", "start": 653.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "And in our lab,", "start": 658.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we are focused on taking fat", "start": 660.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and reprogramming", "start": 662.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "mounds of fat", "start": 664.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into fountains of youthful cells --", "start": 666.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "cells that we may use", "start": 670.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to then form other,", "start": 672.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "more specialized, cells,", "start": 674.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which one day may be used as cell transplants.", "start": 676.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If this research is successful,", "start": 680.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it may then reduce the need", "start": 683.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to research and sacrifice", "start": 686.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "human embryos.", "start": 688.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Indeed, there is a lot of hype, but also hope", "start": 692.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that the promise of stem cells", "start": 695.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "will one day provide cures", "start": 697.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for a whole range of conditions.", "start": 699.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Heart disease, stroke, diabetes,", "start": 701.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "spinal cord injury, muscular dystrophy,", "start": 704.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "retinal eye diseases --", "start": 706.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are any of these conditions", "start": 709.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "relevant, personally, to you?", "start": 711.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In May 2006,", "start": 714.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "something horrible happened to me.", "start": 717.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was about to start a robotic operation,", "start": 720.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but stepping out of the elevator", "start": 722.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into the bright and glaring lights of the operating room,", "start": 724.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I realized", "start": 727.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that my left visual field", "start": 729.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was fast collapsing into darkness.", "start": 731.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Earlier that week,", "start": 734.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I had taken a rather hard knock", "start": 736.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "during late spring skiing -- yes, I fell.", "start": 738.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And I started to see floaters and stars,", "start": 741.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which I casually dismissed", "start": 743.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as too much high-altitude sun exposure.", "start": 745.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What happened to me", "start": 748.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "might have been catastrophic,", "start": 750.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "if not for the fact", "start": 752.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that I was in reach of good surgical access.", "start": 754.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And I had my vision restored,", "start": 756.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but not before a prolonged period of convalescence --", "start": 758.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "three months --", "start": 761.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a head down position.", "start": 763.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This experience", "start": 765.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "taught me to empathize more with my patients,", "start": 767.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and especially those with retinal diseases.", "start": 770.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "37 million people worldwide", "start": 774.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are blind,", "start": 776.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and 127 million more", "start": 778.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "suffer from impaired vision.", "start": 781.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Stem cell-derived retinal transplants,", "start": 784.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "now in a research phase,", "start": 787.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "may one day restore vision,", "start": 789.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or part vision,", "start": 791.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to millions of patients with retinal diseases worldwide.", "start": 793.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Indeed, we live", "start": 797.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in both challenging", "start": 799.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as well as exciting times.", "start": 801.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "As the world population ages,", "start": 805.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "scientists are racing", "start": 808.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to discover new ways", "start": 810.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to enhance the power of the body", "start": 812.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to heal itself through stem cells.", "start": 814.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It is a fact", "start": 817.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that when our organs or tissues are injured,", "start": 819.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "our bone marrow", "start": 822.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "releases stem cells", "start": 824.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into our circulation.", "start": 826.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And these stem cells", "start": 828.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "then float in the bloodstream", "start": 830.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and hone in to damaged organs", "start": 832.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to release growth factors", "start": 835.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to repair the damaged tissue.", "start": 837.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Stem cells may be used as building blocks", "start": 839.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to repair damaged scaffolds within our body,", "start": 842.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "or to provide new liver cells", "start": 846.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to repair damaged liver.", "start": 848.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "As we speak, there are 117 or so clinical trials", "start": 851.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "researching the use of stem cells", "start": 854.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for liver diseases.", "start": 857.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What lies ahead?", "start": 859.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Heart disease", "start": 861.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the leading cause of death worldwide.", "start": 863.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "1.1 million Americans", "start": 865.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "suffer heart attacks yearly.", "start": 867.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "4.8 million", "start": 870.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "suffer cardiac failure.", "start": 872.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Stem cells may be used", "start": 874.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to deliver growth factors", "start": 876.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to repair damaged heart muscle", "start": 878.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or be differentiated", "start": 880.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "into heart muscle cells", "start": 882.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to restore heart function.", "start": 884.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There are 170 clinical trials", "start": 886.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "investigating the role of stem cells in heart disease.", "start": 889.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "While still in a research phase,", "start": 893.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "stem cells may one day herald", "start": 896.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a quantum leap in the field of cardiology.", "start": 899.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Stem cells provide hope for new beginnings --", "start": 903.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "small, incremental steps,", "start": 906.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "cells rather than organs,", "start": 909.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "repair rather than replacement.", "start": 912.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Stem cell therapies", "start": 915.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "may one day reduce the need for donor organs.", "start": 918.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Powerful new technologies", "start": 922.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "always present enigmas.", "start": 924.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "As we speak,", "start": 926.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the world's first human embryonic stem cell trial for spinal cord injury", "start": 928.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is currently underway", "start": 931.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "following the USFDA approval.", "start": 933.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And in the U.K.,", "start": 936.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "neural stem cells to treat stroke", "start": 938.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are being investigated in a phase one trial.", "start": 940.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The research success that we celebrate today", "start": 944.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has been made possible", "start": 947.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "by the curiosity and contribution and commitment", "start": 949.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "of individual scientists", "start": 953.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and medical pioneers.", "start": 955.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Each one has his story.", "start": 957.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "My story has been about my journey", "start": 960.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "from organs to cells --", "start": 963.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a journey through controversy,", "start": 965.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "inspired by hope --", "start": 967.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "hope that, as we age,", "start": 969.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "you and I may one day celebrate longevity", "start": 972.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "with an improved quality of life.", "start": 975.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you.", "start": 977.26, "duration": 2.0}]